BIRNIN KEBBI – A total of 57 party delegates on Sunday elected Abubakar Aliyu Dangadima (Tukuran Gwandu) as the sole candidate of the New Nigeria people’s party (NNPP) to ply the party’s ticket as hopeful of Birnin Kebbi, Kalgo and Bunza federal constituency. The chairman electoral committee of the party Usman Ibrahim Kangiwa who declared him the winner of the primaries said a total of 87 delegates drawn from the three local governments were accredited out of which 57 cast their ballots to formally give legal backing to the primaries. The primary election was conducted before INEC official Bilyaminu Malami security agents and a huge number of party stalwarts, party chairmen of the party and delegates. -Advertisement- Speaking shortly after his affirmation Abubakar said that he joined politics after active service to contribute his quota to the country’s progress and of his party and his would-be constituents,Tukura who described NNPP as a third force stated that his party has come to rescue Nigeria from the poor leadership of APC and PDP then saying hunger, insecurity has become endemic under the ruling APC in the country. He added that,NNPP has the popularity it required because their presidential aspirant Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso is a famous politician and a detribilised leader who carry every region in the country.